table pathlib_extra1411.pathlib_mro_and_name:
  description: "pathlib class MRO length and class name length checks — wave 541 extra1411. pathlib.PurePath.__mro__.__len__()==2 ([PurePath, object]; shallowest chain in this batch; PurePath is the pure-Python abstract base for path objects and subclasses object directly). pathlib.PurePosixPath.__mro__.__len__()==3 ([PurePosixPath, PurePath, object]). pathlib.Path.__mro__.__len__()==3 ([Path, PurePath, object]). pathlib.PosixPath.__mro__.__len__()==5 ([PosixPath, Path, PurePosixPath, PurePath, object]; deepest chain in this batch due to multiple inheritance levels). pathlib.PureWindowsPath.__name__.__len__()==15 ('PureWindowsPath'=15 chars; longest name in this batch). pathlib.PurePosixPath.__name__.__len__()==13 ('PurePosixPath'=13 chars). pathlib.PurePath.__name__.__len__()==8. pathlib.PosixPath.__name__.__len__()==9. All verified with Python 3.14.3."
